# Public repo hygiene (Conductor maintainers)

Conductor is **public OSS**. Tracked files must not name Vault & Compass portfolio
products, private application repos, or links to private downstream work.

## Never commit

- Portfolio or venture codenames (internal app/repo names)
- Private `github.com/vaultcompasshq/<app>` links (except this repo)
- Dogfood notes tied to a specific private repo
- Domain-specific test fixtures that fingerprint a private app
- Session handoffs, audits, plans — use gitignored `.local/` or `TODO.local.md`

## Write instead

Generic placeholders (`private downstream app repo`, synthetic paths). Describe the
**pattern**, not the source product.

## Before commit or PR

```bash
pnpm validate:portfolio-names
```

CI uses a **hash blocklist only** — no plaintext codenames in the repo. To add a
hash, see the comment at the top of `scripts/validate-no-portfolio-names.mjs`.

Policy: [docs/release/public-content-policy.md](../../docs/release/public-content-policy.md)
